name: Say's Phoebe
overview: Often pump their  tails when on a wire, fence post and or a low bush. When they look for food they often perch around their eye levels and jump to snatch flying insects. During migration these birds can be found thousands of miles out of range. Least concern.
habitat: Undaunted by people and usually build nests on buildings. Live in open country  such in canyons and sagebrush and they avoid forests.
